This is a first pass over NUISANCE FlatTree_VARS. It uses pdg_vert for primary strange content, final state pdg for final Lambda content, and a p plus pi-minus proxy requiring primary or final hyperon evidence for S0.

The primary mechanism macro keeps the Lambda-topology sample inclusive, then reports the selected sample by primary strange origin and generator Mode category with sample, generator, knob, beam_polarity, and statistical uncertainty columns. It first restricts all reported counts and spectra to the selected non-zero MicroBooNE NuMI flux envelope and multiplies event weights by the selected NuMI flux histogram divided by its mean bin content over the flat proposal range. It refuses to run if it cannot load that envelope or the sample has no Enu_true branch. If reduced topology flags such as topology_nominal_flag or fiducial_vertex_flag are not present, it falls back to a FlatTree proxy requiring final-state Lambda plus visible-proxy proton and pi-minus, and prints that caveat in the ROOT metadata and terminal output.

The nuclear-exit macro uses the same flat-proposal NuMI flux reweight and writes sample, generator, knob, and beam_polarity columns. It requires explicit Stage B branches such as n_exitp plus pdg_exit, or nuclear_exit_n plus nuclear_exit_pdg, and it refuses to use final-state pdg as a nuclear-exit proxy.

The detached Lambda topology still needs the reduced ntuple fields from CONTEXT: nuclear-exit strange species, Lambda decay vertex, daughter ancestry, fiducial flags, decay length, and truth-visible containment flags.
